<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n53023h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53023h">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53023h"> 23(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> tell name to foe = lache</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">To tell one&apos;s name to an enemy was reckoned, in those days of heroism, a manifest evasion of fighting him; for if it was once known, that friendship subsisted, of old, between the ancestors of the combatants, the battle immediately ceased; and the ancient amity of their forefathers was renewed. <mark><i>A man who tells his name to his enemy</i>, was of old an igominious term for a coward</mark>. <small> James MacPherson, <a name="JMPO" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JMPO"><cite title="source">The Poems of Ossian</cite></a> (1806) <font size="-1">CARTHON</font> Book I, 200n</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
